Sabse badi baat jo yaad rakhni hai — teen magic questions poochh apne aap se:

Array/string sorted hai aur pair dhundhna hai? → Opposite ends
Linked list ka problem hai? → Fast & Slow (99% cases)
"Longest / shortest / minimum subarray ya substring" likha hai? → Sliding Window



Opposite ends
L=0, R=last
Array is sorted
"Find a pair" with sum/product condition
Check palindrome
"Maximize / minimize" area, distance
Reverse something in-place
3Sum, 4Sum pattern


Fast & slow
slow+1, fast+2
Linked list — almost always this
"Detect cycle" — dead giveaway
Find middle of list
Remove Nth node from end
"Does it loop?" type question
Happy number problem



Sliding window
Both start at 0
"Longest subarray / substring"
"Smallest subarray" with condition
"Subarray of size k"
Contiguous elements matter
Max/min within a window
Count subarrays with condition